  [1] Just kidding obviously. The next Money Stuff will be, you know, when =
you get it. Will it be Tuesday? It might be Tuesday! Who can predict that f=
ar ahead.


  [2] There are a million sorts of lawyers in the world and this is a wild =
oversimplification, but at big law firms like Musk=E2=80=99s and Twitter=E2=
=80=99s, there are mostly these two sorts. Plus restructuring lawyers, who =
are kind of in between. Also, again, this is terribly oversimplified and st=
ereotyped in a way that is not generally true, but that I suspect has some =
important truth *here*.


  [3] A footnote adds: =E2=80=9CIf Defendants refuse to close because the d=
ebt has not funded, Twitter could only pursue a claim for breach against X =
Holdings I, Inc. The remedy for such breach is that Twitter may terminate t=
he Merger Agreement and seek a Parent Termination Fee of $1 billion under S=
ection 8.3(b). The Merger Agreement expressly caps the amount under Section=
 8.3(c) even in the case of =E2=80=98knowing and intentional breach.=E2=80=
=99 Consistent with that cap, Musk signed a Limited Guarantee of the Parent=
 Termination Fee in the amount of $1 billion, which itself has an express c=
ap at that amount as well as a non-recourse provision.=E2=80=9D


  [4] The banks=E2=80=99 commitments are governed by New York law, and he=
=E2=80=99d have to sue in New York. She couldn=E2=80=99t just tell him =E2=
=80=9Csue those banks in my courtroom and we=E2=80=99ll see what happens.=
=E2=80=9D


  [5] Lauren Hirsch of the New York Times pointed out on Twitter: "Tesla's =
earnings are Oct 19. I assume Musk is in a quiet period now, which would me=
an he can't sell more stock until after. So, another thing a delay might al=
low him is the ability to raise more cash via stock sale." This is a fair p=
oint; perhaps he *can't* actually get his $33 billion together on quite suc=
h short notice, though I bet some bank could bridge that with a two-week ma=
rgin loan if he really wanted to get it done.


