background-color: #ccc;">  discussed on Wednesday</a>, they have to fund th=
e debt (with their own money) even if they don=E2=80=99t have a chance to=
=C2=A0market it first. And selling this debt =E2=80=94=C2=A0doing the paper=
work, getting Twitter and Musk to work together on=C2=A0marketing materials=
, holding meetings with investors, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0in three weeks would=
 be awfully aggressive. =E2=80=9CThe banks, including Bank of America, Barc=
lays, and Japanese bank and Morgan Stanley-investor MUFG, are not expected =
to attempt to raise $12.5bn of the debt through public or private debt mark=
ets before the takeover is finalised, as is usually the case in a leveraged=
 buyout,=E2=80=9D says <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/29299349.282523/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvZWY2MTBmZjMtZDQxOC=
00MjIxLTlkZmUtNGQ4OWI0MTI2ZTM1/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2b03385d" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 the Financial Times</a>. The banks plan to bridge this debt themselves (an=
d then try to sell it later, after closing).</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So I don=E2=80=99t quite know why it would tak=
e three weeks for them to find the money. They=E2=80=99re banks, they have =
lots of money. In <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
29299349.282523/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZG9jdW1lbnRjbG91ZC5vcmcvZG9jdW1lbnRzLzIzMTI=
2Njk3LXR3aXR0ZXItcmVzcG9uc2UtdG8tbW90aW9uLXRvLXN0YXktdHdpdHRlci12LW11c2s/60=
