ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> their response</a> to Musk=E2=80=
=99s motion yesterday, Twitter=E2=80=99s lawyers said:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Nor have they supplied any reason =
to believe that closing cannot be achieved in the days before trial. Just t=
his morning, a corporate representative for one of the lending banks testif=
ied that Mr. Musk has yet to send them a borrowing notice and has not other=
wise communicated to them that he intends to close the transaction, let alo=
ne on any particular timeline. The bank further testified that the main tas=
k necessary to close the deal=E2=80=94memorializing the debt financing=E2=
=80=94could have happened in July but didn=E2=80=99t because Mr. Musk purpo=
rted to terminate the deal.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think it is probably a=C2=A0<em>little=C2=A0=
</em>cute for Twitter to say that Musk=E2=80=99s banks haven=E2=80=99t yet =
put up the money because he hasn=E2=80=99t yet asked them to, but the timel=
ine is a little weird.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If Elon Musk walked into=C2=A0court and handed=
 Twitter=E2=80=99s lawyers a sack full of $46=C2=A0billion in cash, that wo=
uld not be quite sufficient to close this deal, but it would be pretty clos=
e. There=E2=80=99d be some paperwork, some filings, some administrative wor=
k left to do; it would take a few days of lawyers=E2=80=99 time. But practi=
cally speaking if he put up the $46 billion this would be over. He=E2=80=99=
s the richest person in the world and can surely get together his $33 billi=
on portion of it.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgr=
ound-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a> His banks are really big banks, and can surely get together their $13 =
billion portion. Again, might take a few days, some paperwork, but that is =
the business they have chosen; you can=E2=80=99t really go around being lik=
e =E2=80=9CI promise Morgan Stanley will give me $13 billion but we need to=
 wait until it gets its paycheck at the end of the month.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So when Musk told Twitter that he wants to cal=
l off the lawsuit and close the merger, Twitter understandably said, yes, r=
ight, show us the $46 billion and we=E2=80=99ll get right on that. And Musk=
 said, no, let=E2=80=99s call off the lawsuit <em>first</em>, and then you=
=E2=80=99ll get your money by the end of the month. I don=E2=80=99t think t=
hat Musk was=C2=A0<em>wrong=C2=A0</em>to ask for that; I think that calling=
 off the lawsuit probably=C2=A0<em>will=C2=A0</em>make the closing easier a=
nd smoother and more pleasant and possibly even faster. I can see why the j=
udge granted Musk=E2=80=99s request. But I can also see why Twitter is nerv=
ous. Twitter would be happier if it could see the money. And Musk changes h=
is mind a lot.</p>
